@thechosenone gotta respectfully disagree there... the story was a lot different... the cut wasn't a small thing... it was a drastic change, and a TON of story content, including Cyborg playing a way deeper integral role in the team, his moments before the car crash, Darkseid actually appearing, Superman being brought back in a different way, The Flash discovering Speed Force.  There was over an hour of story content that was stripped out.

Also, Batman vs Superman Ultimate Cut is a much more complete movie than the theatrical version.

I'd say that Zack's biggest flaw is that he's a very detail oriented director that works best when he does long epics.  When a studio forces him to cram everything from a 3 hour movie down to less than 2 hours... it suffers a lot.

@soy boy with a big bag of chips and a big heart No, unless Billy has something shielding him. Black Adam might say it sometimes repeatedly but the rule should apply to him too, if he says it once, he's dead. I'm hoping when we do get Adam, he's alive for a while. He's too good of a villain to have him be one off or dead so soon. We should see Khandaq. I think The Rock could make a badass villain too.
The Rock was casted in 2014. If Shazam isn't received well or flops, It'll take even longer to see him I'm sure.
And god damn do I love Black Adam's New 52 look. Half hood, half cape like Shazam's New 52/movie look. I just need to see it in live action.
